title: A checke to Brittanicus, for his palpable flattery and prevarication, in justifying condemned Nat: Fiennes. Published for the present necessary vindication of his traduced iudges, prosecutors, and of truth and publique iustice, till an exact relation of all the proceedings in that triall bee set forth by the councell of warre, and his antagonists for their further justification, and satisfaction of the world, so miserably abused with mis-reports of that action, for which he was condemned.
author: Prynne, William, 1600-1669.
publicationStmtPublisher: Printed by Iohn Dawson for George Hutton,
